In `MainClass.pyi` the `get_user` method is typed as such:
```py
    def get_user(
        self, login: Union[str, _NotSetType] = ...
    ) -> Union[AuthenticatedUser, NamedUser]: ...
```

But I took a look at the implementation and I think the returned type can be better by using [function overloading](https://mypy.readthedocs.io/en/stable/more_types.html#function-overloading):
```py
from typing import overload
...

    @overload
    def get_user(self, login: str
    ) -> NamedUser: ...
    @overload
    def get_user(
        self, login: _NotSetType = ...
    ) -> AuthenticatedUser: ...
    def get_user(
        self, login: Union[str, _NotSetType] = ...
    ) -> Union[AuthenticatedUser, NamedUser]: ...
```

That way if you call it with a `login` mypy knows it returns a `NamedUser`, and if you call without the `login` argument it returns an `AuthenticatedUser`.

Note: this is my current use case but I didn't check to see if other methods could be improved like this.
